<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-827-900  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 827 900.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Oct 30 1989 v6 n43 p44(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Gibson upgrades SpinRite disk-maintenance utility. (GibsonResearch Inc.'s SpinRite II disk-maintenance utility) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Gibson Research Corp. (product enhancement).andO;Product:   SpinRite II (Utility program) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     UpgradingUtility ProgramsHard DiskData Recovery.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Keeping in step with recent advancements in DOS and hard-disk drivetechnology, Gibson Research Inc. recently introduced an updated version ofits SpinRite disk-maintenance utility.andM;Like its predecessor, SpinRite II allows users to perform low-level formatson their hard disks, test and recover damaged sectors, and rescue data fromunreliable regions -- all without destroying data already stored on thedamaged disk, said David Kaye, a spokesperson for the Laguna Hills, Calif.,andO;company.andM;SpinRite II adds to its predecessor's basic functionality with support forthe larger disk-partition sizes (greater than 32M bytes) allowed by both DOS4.0 and third-party partitioning software.andM;The utility also now includes a reporting capability, which allows users tokeep a log of all SpinRite findings in a permanent file on disk, and theability to detect and protect copy-protection software on the hard diskduring low-level formatting.andM;Available now, the $89 software sports an automatic-configuration utilitythat eases installation and includes support for high-performance hard-diskcontrollers.andM;Gibson can be reached at (714) 830-2200.andO;</TEXT></DOC>